i think you meant to just hardcode the paths here?

???

Some kind of squash due to requesting create meson, then remove autoconf?

Assuming you had a bit of a mess trying to re-arrange things, so compared this against https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-fan-presence/+/54519 and https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-fan-presence/+/54615/19.
Well, I suppose, technically, you did not remove autoconf yet, so ideally you would include instructions for both... moving along.

Possibly nit-picky, but eventually I notice that some of these meson* files have 2 blank lines at the end, others have one blank line, ... not even sure if it should have a single blank line, but possibly nice to be consistent.
Realizing that phosphor-power does not do something like this, as far as I know, and then I wonder how you make sure you keep up with the best version.
I didn't type this, it's autogen from the meson wrap command.
I think you're missing a phosphor-logging wrapfile.
since these are all feature flags I think they need to be -Ddisable-control=enabled, etc?
How about we use an ergonomic design and rename the flag to use-json ? enabled by default, so if someone wants to use the deprecated path, they'd have to write -Duse-json=disabled.

what I said stands for json, but also for use-<program> the same pattern could be followed? -Dcontrol-service or -Dcontrol-daemon=enabled by default, and if someone wishes to disable it, it would read -Dcontrol-service=disabled.
yea, renaming to remove the 'disable/enable' in the name works for me.
these would just need to get added if JSON is enabled

you may as well follow what control/Makefile.am did here for which files to include.  So all the json/* files only if JSON is enabled, and 

	argument.cpp \
	fan.cpp \
	manager.cpp \
	utility.cpp \
	preconditions.cpp \
	actions.cpp \
	triggers.cpp \
	zone.cpp


else
needs nlohmann_json_dep, cli11, phosphor_logging as deps
Looks like you forgot to add these?
this is only necessary if fan-presence is enabled.  Is there a way to make it depend on that flag?

other dependencies missing are CLI11 for fanctl and nlohmann-json if json is enabled. Also phosphor-dbus-interfaces. They would need wrapfiles too. phosphor-inventory would be a good reference for that.

looks like the 'if get_option('disable-cooling-type').disabled()' check is missing.

I guess that dir also needs a meson.build
probably needs nlohmann-json (if json enabled) added as a dep
need fmt, phosphor_logging, nlohmann_json, and sdeventplus deps
i think only fanctl uses cli11?
these aren't needed when JSON is enabled.
this is always true since its in the build_tests.enabled(), so may as well just hardcode it and remove line 45.
looks like this needs to be 'phosphor-dbus-interfaces'
need to add the phosphor-fan-control-init  executable here
I don't know why I thought that was a thing.  It isn't.
will change this to just 'json-control' and have it be a feature
Need to check for the directory to be present being installing it, or else bitbake will complain about the empty subdir being there but not in FILES.
Everthing appears to work, so going to go ahead and merge to finally get it in.
